senate bill 1618, Title 3 Section 301. Per Section 301, Paragraph (a)(2)(C) of S.1618, Passed 
by Senate, May 12, 1998. as well as all federal and state laws regarding email messages 
including the California Business and Professions Code 17538.4 as amended by Assembly Bill 
1676 (1998) (approved by Governor, September 26, 1998) and cannot be considered as SPAM 
since it includes a remove mechanism (at least 2 possibilities plus personal assistance in case of 
any problem) as well as the real contact information and LIST owner address.

